                    <comment id="12662394" author="jukkaz" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2009 15:20:27 +0000"  >How about this alternative patch that makes sanityCheck() directly throw a RepositoryException? This way we don&amp;#39;t need to explicitly catch and rethrow the exception.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Note that I also removed the sanityCheck() call from a few protected getter methods. Public methods that cause those getters to be invoked have already called sanityCheck, so it&amp;#39;s safe to drop these extra calls.</comment>
                    <comment id="12662400" author="fmeschbe" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2009 15:30:04 +0000"  >Looks good to me, too, and makes perfect sense.</comment>
                    <comment id="12662424" author="jukkaz" created="Fri, 9 Jan 2009 16:51:14 +0000"  >Patch applied in revision 733080. Targeting for 1.5.1.</comment>
                    <comment id="12662990" author="gjoseph" created="Mon, 12 Jan 2009 16:30:21 +0000"  >I might be wrong, but I seem to remember this is the exception i got with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1778&quot; title=&quot;BindableRepositoryFactory doesn&amp;#39;t handle repository shutdown&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-1778&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which might thus be irrelevant now ?</comment>
